properties.value:
the original
Hagboard
built by Hagbard (Org: Bruderschaft der Alten)
thx to Destrin (ODY) for his voxel magic
Thanks for choosing to fly with style on a Hagboard.
The Hagboard can be flown using a remote controller,
just stand on the back of the board,
look down and "activate" the RC using the "F" key.
This should lock you from walking of the board
and the usual piloting controls should work.
After landing, look on the RC again and deactivate it using the "F" key.

Tips:
* In case you crash and fly of the board or any other reason you want to end your pilot control session
,press "CTRL+Backspace", to force the control session to be stopped.

* Hagboards can reach an insane speed. Above 1800kmh,
you will see it start glowing in a red color due to the air resistance.
Don't worry, usually it will not take any damage at this point. If you go even faster,
damage to elements can occur so always carry some scrap in your inventory.

* The Hagboard can be refueled mid flight, just look at the atmorspheric fuel tank
(it shimmers through the voxels at the front) and refuel it using the refuel tool

* If you want to go really fast, try to fly at a steady altitude below 800m,
then accelerate (without gaining altitude at first!) Avoid any control movement.
The board will start gaining some altitude after a while, but still do not touch the controls.
Just let it accelerate and enjoy.

And now hop on.. let the fun begin
